The paper deals with the approximability of the metric TSP, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, graph theory, and optimization, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.GT, and cs.LG. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper. Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely as they deal with approximation algorithms and computational complexity.
